To find the sum of natural numbers from 100 to 500 in C, you can use a loop to iterate through the numbers and accumulate the sum. Here's a simple program to do that:

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int sum = 0;
    for(int i = 100; i <= 500; i++) {
        sum += i;
    }
    printf("The sum of natural numbers from 100 to 500 is: %d\n", sum);
    return 0;
}
```

